{
  "texts": [
    "On the other hand, producing a large number of real-world samples is prohibitively expansive 55.",
    "To be compatible with the previous dataset, we adopted the same technique for simulating the dynamic behaviour of the samples, i.e., dynamic Lattice Element Method (dLEM) 56, 57.",
    "The lattice element method (LEM) consists of mesoscale models that decompose a material sample into lattice cells.",
    "The lattice nodes can be considered as the centres of the lattice particles, which are connected by beams that can carry normal force, shear force, and bending moment.",
    "Cracks can be represented by simply removing the lattice particles."
  ]
}